    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix path loss calculation precision in get_PL function\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_PL()` function in LTE UE measurements was experiencing precision loss due to integer arithmetic operations. This caused incorrect path loss calculations that affected uplink power control algorithms.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_ESTIMATION/lte_ue_measurements.c`: Refactored `get_PL()` function to use explicit 32-bit integer arithmetic and clearer variable naming to prevent precision loss during path loss calculations.\n\n### Reproduction\nUsers may observe unexpected behavior in uplink power control, with UEs transmitting at incorrect power levels. This can manifest as:\n- Poor uplink SNR performance\n- Increased uplink interference\n- UE failing to establish connections in poor coverage conditions\n\nThe issue is most noticeable when `rx_total_gain_dB` and `referenceSignalPower` values result in intermediate calculations that lose precision due to integer division truncation.\n\n"
}